>
>I have a problem with my westy that Ive been trying to
>fix for 5 years. (its just a pain, not too bad)
>
>For the first few minutes after a cold start it runs
>fine (you can mat it and the power is constant and
>clean). After a few minutes it hesitates at low rpm
>high load (any gear same condition). At high RPM and
>lower load, it doenst seem to hesitate (miss?).  It
>misses intermittantly while idling.  Runs great, does
>not use oil, decent gas mileage (better than my solex'd
>71)
>
>List of things Ive tested very well:
>-Reset timing.
>-Changed Condenser/Coil/points/wires/plugs/rotor
>-Replaced Air filter (seems to make it somewhat better)
>
>-Sealed up all vacuum lines/replaced lines and tie
>wrapped in place.
>-Tried another ECU.
>-Oil pressure is fine
>-Checked Temp sensor (volt/ohmmeter).
>-Replaced Fuel filter
>-Clutch (mechanic told me the seal was leaking and
>hesitation was due to the clutch was slipping)
>-EGR disconnected (by previous owner) mechanical valve
>position makes no difference.
>
>Things I have checked reasonably well:
>-Mass flow sensor seems fine (volt/ohmmeter tested)
>-Auxilary air regulator (tested seals and opens)
>-Cold start injector makes no difference connected or
>not.
>-System voltage (stable no battery problems either)
>-Wiring harness connectors, grounds
>
>Things I have not checked since I dont think they will
>make a difference
>-Fuel pressure
>-Injector output rates
>
>I keep trying to think what would cause this after a
>few minutes of driving (in winter I can almost get 4
>miles before it starts).
>Help??!!
>Many thanks
>Logan Grauer
>Regina, Saskatchewan, Canada.
